divs: Sighting Detailswas walking my dog at 9:30pm looking up at the stars as i normally do. dog was done with business started walking to front of house when i noticed a bright star @ 9:45 pm that i though was moving and it was i ran in house put dog upin less then 15 seconds and grabbed my 15x70 astronomy binoculars by the door and watched it speed by it did not blink looked like a satellite but lower and moved a lot faster then the ones iv seen in past lostsight of it when trees on hill blocked view. saw about 2-3 mins of it.
trends: There have been 20 other sightings in Bristol
There were no other sightings in Bristol on or around July 17th 2011
Summary: bright starlike object moving at a very fast speed east to west
